race.comment: ARTIE LADY (14) set to peak fourth-up as she gets out to this trip for the first time. Snagged back from the wide gate and happy to overlook the poor eighth over 1420m at Lismore. Drawn to get the right run today and can give this a mighty shake at the each-way odds. DAMONS ON A BENDER (10) got off the mark at start two with an effortless victory as fav over 1250m at Taree on the soft (6) track. Doesn't get the same map favours and not to be overlooked. SMOKEY SAINT (15) placed at this course and distance and comes here deep into the prep. Caught the eye late when fourth over 1400m at Taree. Top-three player from the barrier. CALEDONIAN (8) failed to go the good early tempo when over-raced throughout to finish a dismal last over 1605m at Coffs Harbour. Blinkers come off and assess on the win two back over the mile.
